@Situation:	Chi and Mot sit at kitchen table , hold book together. There is a dim light over the table. The tv is on in the background
@Comment:	Chi points to each word as he reads. Chi is a so-so reader. What sticks out are some of Mot's clues-they are semantic , with no relation to the story or to reading. Once , though , MOT points to picture for (ice cream) cone , and she sounds out most of the problem words in the post-food section (which goes very slowly). Mot helps when Chi pauses for a long time or asks what does this say.
